---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";

const title = "CV · Usman Shahid";
const description =
  "Full CV of Usman Shahid — Staff Site Reliability Engineer at Careem. 11+ years scaling cloud infrastructure. Download as PDF.";
---

<Base title={title} description={description} path="/cv/">
  <article class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
    <header class="mb-10 pb-8 border-b border-[--color-border]">
      <h1
        class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-[--color-text] mb-2"
      >
        Usman Shahid
      </h1>
      <p class="text-[--color-text-muted] mb-1">
        <a href="mailto:u.manshahid@gmail.com">u.manshahid@gmail.com</a> ·
        +971-52-932-8265 ·
        <a
          href="https://github.com/codemug"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">github.com/codemug</a
        > ·
        <a
          href="https://linkedin.com/in/u-manshahid"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener noreferrer">linkedin.com/in/u-manshahid</a
        >
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-[--color-text-muted] mb-6">
        Open to relocation: EU / UK / Ireland / Netherlands / Germany &mdash;
        visa sponsorship required. Currently Dubai (GMT+4).
      </p>
      <a
        href="/cv-usman-shahid.pdf"
        class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-[--color-accent] text-[--color-bg] px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium hover:no-underline hover:opacity-90"
      >
        Download PDF
      </a>
    </header>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2
        class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[--color-accent] mb-3"
      >
        Summary
      </h2>
      <p class="text-[--color-text-muted] leading-relaxed">
        Staff <strong class="text-[--color-text]"
          >Site Reliability Engineer</strong
        > and Technical Lead with <strong class="text-[--color-text]"
          >11+ years</strong
        > scaling resilient, cost-effective cloud infrastructure for
        high-traffic services. Currently running a self-service AI Agent
        Platform with Model Context Protocol (MCP) tool-calling, multi-agent
        orchestration, and human-in-the-loop (HITL) approval flows &mdash;
        <strong class="text-[--color-text]">~200K requests/day</strong>,
        <strong class="text-[--color-text]">~800 registered tools</strong>,
        <strong class="text-[--color-text]">~60 production agents</strong>
        &mdash; bridging classic SRE discipline with the agentic-AI era.
        Track record: <strong class="text-[--color-text]"
          >40% EKS cost reduction</strong
        > via Karpenter / ARM / Spot / VPA, <strong class="text-[--color-text]"
          >99.99% uptime</strong
        > consolidating 12 API gateways to Kong at ~10k RPS, <strong
          class="text-[--color-text]">300+ microservices</strong
        > migrated to EKS. Polyglot &mdash; production Go, Python, Java, and
        C#. Daily AI-tooling user (Claude, Cursor, Copilot, Gemini).
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-10">
      <h2
        class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-[--color-accent] mb-3"
      >
        Work Experience
      </h2>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div>
          <div
            class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-x-3 gap-y-1 mb-1"
          >
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[--color-text]">
              Staff Site Reliability Engineer · Careem
            </h3>
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[--color-text-dim]"
              >Jan 2023 — Present</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-[--color-text-muted] mb-3">
            Technical Lead and SRE Architect mentoring a team focused on
            infrastructure provisioning and developer experience.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-5 marker:text-[--color-text-dim] text-[--color-text-muted] text-[15px] leading-relaxed"
          >
            <li>
              Designed and built a <strong class="text-[--color-text]"
                >self-service AI Agent Platform</strong
              > with MCP tool-calling, multi-agent orchestration, and HITL
              approval flows for internal infrastructure-support workflows
              &mdash; ~200K req/day, ~800 registered tools, ~60 agents in
              production. Engineering teams contribute their own tools and
              agents.
            </li>
            <li>
              <strong class="text-[--color-text]"
                >Slashed EKS cluster costs by 40%</strong
              > via resource-optimization program — Karpenter consolidation,
              migration to ARM &amp; Spot nodes, VPA, and custom scheduling
              (FinOps at scale).
            </li>
            <li>
              Consolidated <strong class="text-[--color-text]"
                >12 legacy API gateways (~10k RPS) onto a single Kong gateway
                with 99.99% uptime</strong
              > during cutover; built a GitOps-driven bespoke control plane for
              API route management.
            </li>
            <li>
              Designed and deployed a fully automated cloud-resource
              provisioning platform with GitOps (Terraform + Terragrunt) &mdash;
              provisioning time for new services from days to minutes.
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div>
          <div
            class="flex flex-wrap items-baseline gap-x-3 gap-y-1 mb-1"
          >
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[--color-text]">
              Senior Site Reliability Engineer · Careem
            </h3>
            <span class="text-xs font-mono text-[--color-text-dim]"
              >Dec 2020 — Jan 2023</span
            >
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-[--color-text-muted] mb-3">
            Led migration of 300+ microservices from legacy AWS to AWS EKS.
          </p>
          <ul
            class="space-y-2 list-disc pl-5 marker:text-[--color-text-dim] text-[--color-text-muted] text-[15px] leading-relaxed"
          >
            <li>
              Engineered automated provisioning of multiple EKS clusters with
              Terraform + Terragrunt &mdash; repeatable, auditable
              infrastructure foundation.
            </li>
            <li>
              Provisioned centralized API Gateways using Kong with a GitOps
              control plane for API route management.
            </li>
            <li>
              Built the observability stack with <strong
                class="text-[--color-text]"
                >Prometheus, Thanos, and Grafana</strong
              > &mdash; high-cardinality metric storage, SLO dashboards, cost
              tracking across the EKS fleet.
            </li>
            <li>
              Improved deployment velocity and safety via service mesh
